	<div type="translation" resp="part:argr">
            <p rend="stanza" n="1">At times overgrown by <gap reason="illegible"/>, at times disappearing in pebbles and sand, at times spreading out its pure and cool water, the Ganges gushes forth here, as though <foreign>maṅga</foreign>-armed!</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhabra1970_01">
            <p rend="stanza" n="1">Gushing forth is this (stream), purifying as the Ganges, at some places bedecked with bright lilies and lotus flowers, at some places bubbling out from pebbles and sand, (and) at some places spreading out its pure and cool water.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p><bibl><ptr target="bib:Chhabra1970_01"/></bibl> pointed out that the inscription is inspired by Kālidāsa's <title>Raghuvaṁśa</title>, canto 13, verses 54–57.</p>
         </div>
